tldr: The user requested a review of the sleep questionnaire application against
  its acceptance criteria and the implementation of missing features. The agent
  successfully implemented a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection,
  insufficient sleep syndrome detection, outbound resource links, weighted EDS
  scoring, full CSV export, pain/chronic fatigue screening, and medical/mental
  health history sections.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review and implementation task for
  a sleep questionnaire application. The agent first analyzed the provided
  documentation and existing codebase to identify gaps against the acceptance
  criteria. A detailed plan was then created, outlining eight key missing
  features. The agent proceeded to implement each feature sequentially, starting
  with high-priority items like a tiredness severity scale with safety warnings
  and specific sleep disorder detections (COMISA, Insufficient Sleep Syndrome).
  Other implementations included weighted EDS scoring, adding external resource
  links, expanding the CSV data export to include all responses, and
  incorporating medical/mental health history questions. The approach involved
  modifying data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation
  logic for each new feature, ensuring the application now more fully meets the
  specified requirements.
